   ## Why It Matters
   Explain why this topic is useful in real work.

   ## Core Concepts
   Break down the important concepts clearly.

   ## How It Works
   Explain the actual working flow or mechanism.

   ## Important Commands / Syntax
   Include commands, configuration examples, or syntax if relevant.

   ## Examples
   Add practical examples that make the concept easier to understand.

   ## Benefits
   List the main advantages.

   ## Drawbacks / Limitations
   Explain the flaws, trade-offs, and things people usually ignore.

   ## Hidden Details / Caveats
   Add deeper details, gotchas, edge cases, and practical warnings.

   ## Common Mistakes
   Explain mistakes beginners commonly make and how to avoid them.

   ## Best Practices
   Give practical advice for using this correctly.

   ## Troubleshooting
   Add common problems and fixes if relevant.

   ## Interview Notes
   Add concise interview-focused points if this is a technical topic.

   ## Related Topics
   Link or mention related notes in the folder.

